{
  "measure": {
    "SessionKey": "2019R1",
    "MeasurePrefix": "SB",
    "MeasureNumber": 1045,
    "CatchLine": "Authorizes city or county to adopt property tax exemption in amount not to exceed $300,000 of assessed value of principal place of residence used by homeowner to rent space in residence through public or nonprofit home share program to individuals seeking such space.",
    "MinorityCatchLine": null,
    "MeasureSummary": "\tAuthorizes city or county to adopt property tax exemption \t<i>for portion</i>] <b>in amount not to exceed $300,000 of assessed value</b> of principal place of residence used by homeowner to rent space in residence <b>through public or nonprofit home share program</b> to individuals seeking such space. \t<i>Provides that exemption shall be granted as 100 percent exemption for five consecutive years unless city or county adopts other terms.</i>] Provides that \t<i>city or county</i>] <b>adopting jurisdiction</b> must require \t<i>means testing of home share seekers. Requires</i>] home share rental agreement to offer space at rent affordable to home share seekers with income at or below \t<i>level determined by city or county</i>] <b>60 percent of area median income, must prohibit exemption for home share agreements among family members and must specify period for which exemption may be granted</b>. \n\tProvides that \t<i>exemption applies only to tax levy of city or county enacting exemption law and other taxing districts agreeing to grant exemption,</i>] <b>ordinance or resolution granting exemption may not take effect</b> unless rates of taxation of <b>adopting jurisdiction and</b> taxing districts that agree to grant exemption equal 51 percent or more of total combined rate of taxation. \t<i>Requires exemption to be granted to all residences on same terms in effect on date application is submitted.</i>] \n\tProhibits property receiving any other property tax benefit, other than homestead property tax deferral, from being granted home share exemption. Allows \t<i>city or county</i>] <b>adopting jurisdiction</b> to amend \t<i>or terminate</i>] exemption, subject to approval process of taxing districts described above, <b>or repeal exemption,</b> but provides that residences granted exemption continue to receive exemption under terms in effect at time exemption was first granted. \n\t<b>Sets cap of 500 homes that may be granted exemption statewide in any property tax year.</b> \n\tSunsets authority of city or county to adopt exemption \t<i>or deferral on June 30</i>] <b>that becomes effective after January 31</b>, 2027. Repeals exemption program on January 2, 2029. Provides that residences granted exemption before repeal date continue to receive exemption \t<i>under terms in effect at time granted</i>] <b>if term extends past repeal date</b>. \n\tTakes effect on 91st day following adjournment sine die.",
    "CurrentVersion": "A",
    "RelatingToFull": "Relating to the taxation of property used in a home share program; and prescribing an effective date.",
    "RelatingTo": "Relating to the taxation of property used in a home share program; and prescribing an effective date.",
